The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs 

 The division bench of Justice A.K. Basu and Justice K. Mukherjee on Wednesday rejected the bail plea of Sanjay Kedia, the managing director and CEO of Xponse Technology. He was arrested by the Narcotics Control Bureau on February 12 for allegedly peddling drugs abroad. The Drug Enforcement Agency of the US had tipped off the Indian agency about Kedia. 

 The door of a locker at the New Ballygunge branch of Bank of India was found broken on Wednesday morning. The valuables that had been kept in it were missing. One of the window grilles of the bank was missing and the locker room door was open. Attempts had been made to open the other lockers. Police suspect the involvement of employees.

 Subodh Rajmistri and Mohan Dey were killed and Joydev Dey was injured after being hit by a milk van on Madhusudan Banerjee Road in Nimta on Wednesday morning. According to police, the incident took place around 6 am after the driver lost control of the van. Subodh, a vegetable vendor, was on a bicycle, while Mohan was standing by the side of the road. The van driver fled.

 Swarup Chandra Paul, in his mid-60s, was run over by a truck at the intersection of Raja Manindra Road and Tallah Park Avenue on Wednesday morning. He was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he succumbed to his injuries. The driver was arrested and the vehicle impounded.

 Peejush Dey was arrested on Wednesday in connection with the murder of Madan Das in the Regent Park area on Tuesday. Dass body was found beside a hydrant with his throat slit. Dey was picked up from a house at Vivekananda Park. Chotka, Dass landlord, was arrested earlier in connection with the murder. Police are on the lookout for prime accused Maharana Saha.

 Lakho Das, 52, an employee of the Howrah Municipal Corporation, died while on duty on Wednesday. He was taken to Howrah general hospital, where he was pronounced dead. 




